Difference between ERC1155 and ERC20
1️⃣ Total Supply in ERC-20
In ERC-20:
	There is only one token type
	The contract tracks one global total supply
Example:
uint256 public totalSupply;
Example scenario:
	Deploy token
	Mint 1,000,000 tokens
Then:
Total Supply = 1,000,000
All wallets hold portions of the same token.
Example:
Wallet	Balance
A	300,000
B	200,000
C	500,000
Total = 1,000,000
✔ Only one supply counter exists.
________________________________________
2️⃣ Total Supply in ERC-1155
In ERC-1155:
	The contract can contain many token IDs
	Each token ID has its own supply
Example:
Token ID 1 → Supply 100
Token ID 2 → Supply 500
Token ID 3 → Supply 1
Example use case:
Token ID	Meaning	Supply
1	Sword	100
2	Shield	500
3	Legendary NFT	1
So supply is per-ID, not global.
________________________________________
3️⃣ Key Difference
Feature	ERC-20	ERC-1155
Token types	1	Many
Supply tracking	Global	Per token ID
Function	totalSupply()	totalSupply(id)
Use cases	Currency / fungible token	Games, NFTs, multi-assets
________________________________________
4️⃣ Code Example
ERC-20
function totalSupply() public view returns (uint256)
Returns:
1000000
________________________________________
ERC-1155
function totalSupply(uint256 id) public view returns (uint256)
Example calls:
totalSupply(1) = 100
totalSupply(2) = 500
totalSupply(3) = 1
________________________________________
5️⃣ Simple Real-World Analogy
ERC-20 = One currency
Like USD
Total supply = all dollars
ERC-1155 = Game inventory system
Item 1 = sword (100)
Item 2 = shield (500)
Item 3 = NFT artifact (1)
Each item has its own supply.
________________________________________
✅ Summary
	ERC-20 → One token, one total supply
	ERC-1155 → Many token IDs, each ID has its own supply
