💡 If you're building tokenized warranties or claims (like your WTYSettlement contract), I can also explain why ERC-1155 is often better than ERC-20 for settlement tokens.
You’re close, but the difference is not about how many people can sell.
Both ERC-20 and ERC-1155 allow any number of people to send/sell tokens to any number of people.
The real difference is the number of token types inside the contract.
Let’s explain it in a very simple way.
________________________________________
1️⃣ ERC-20 (One Token Type)
With ERC-20 there is only ONE token.
Think of it like one currency.
Example:
You create a token called WTY.
Total supply:
1,000 WTY
People hold it like this:
Person	Balance
Alice	300 WTY
Bob	400 WTY
Charlie	300 WTY
Now:
	Alice can send to Bob
	Bob can send to 100 people
	Charlie can sell to anyone
✔ Unlimited transfers
But all tokens are identical.
________________________________________
2️⃣ ERC-1155 (Many Token Types)
With ERC-1155 the contract can contain many different tokens.
Each token has an ID.
Example:
Token ID	Item	Supply
1	Warranty A	100
2	Warranty B	500
3	Special NFT	1
Now people can own different token IDs.
Example balances:
Person	ID 1	ID 2	ID 3
Alice	10	0	0
Bob	5	20	0
Charlie	0	5	1
People can still send tokens to anyone.
Example:
	Alice sends 3 of ID 1 to Bob
	Bob sells 10 of ID 2 to Charlie
	Charlie sells ID 3 NFT to Alice
✔ Again unlimited transfers
________________________________________
3️⃣ The Key Difference
Feature	ERC-20	ERC-1155
Token types	1	Many
Example	One currency	Many items
Supply tracking	One supply	Supply per token ID
________________________________________
4️⃣ Simple Real-World Example
ERC-20
Like money:
All $10 bills are the same
________________________________________
ERC-1155
Like a game inventory:
Sword × 100
Shield × 50
Potion × 1000
Each item is different.
________________________________________
5️⃣ Important Clarification
❌ Not true:
ERC-20 = single person selling
✔ True:
Both standards allow:
	many buyers
	many sellers
	unlimited transfers
The only difference is:
ERC-20 → one token
ERC-1155 → multiple token types
________________________________________
✅ One sentence summary
	ERC-20 → One token shared by everyone.
	ERC-1155 → One contract that can create many different tokens.
